{"title_page": "Emi Shinohara", "text_new": "{{Infobox person\n| name                  = Emi Shinohara\n| image                 = \n| caption               = \n| native_name        = \u7be0\u539f \u6075\u7f8e\n| birth_name             = Emiko Shinohara\n| birth_date             = {{Birth date and age|1963|8|8}}\n| birth_place            = [[Fukushima Prefecture]], [[Japan]]\n| death_date             =  \n| death_place            = \n| other_names           = \n| occupation            = [[Voice actress]] and singer\n| years_active          = 1986-present\n| spouse                = [[Hiroshi Watari]]\n| children              = 1\n| partner               = \n| agent                 = [[81 Produce]]\n| website               =\n}}\n\n{{nihongo|'''Emi Shinohara'''|\u7be0\u539f \u6075\u7f8e|Shinohara Emi|born {{nihongo|'''Emiko Shinohara'''|\u7be0\u539f  \u6075\u7f8e\u5b50|Shinohara Emiko}}, born August 8, 1963}} is a Japanese [[Voice acting in Japan|voice actress]] and singer employed by [[81 Produce]] who is most known for voicing [[Sailor Jupiter]] in the original Japanese anime of ''[[Sailor Moon (TV series)|Sailor Moon]]'' and Kushina Uzumaki in [[List of Naruto: Shippuden episodes|Naruto Shippuden]]. She was born in [[Fukushima Prefecture]] and raised in [[Nagano, Nagano|Nagano]].  She is married to [[tokusatsu]] actor Hiroshi Watari. She shares a birthday with fellow ''Sailor Moon'' star [[Rica Fukami]], who voiced [[Sailor Venus]].\n\n==Voice roles==\n*Elizabeth in ''[[Dream Hunter Rem]]'' ''(Debut Role 1986)''\n*B-Ko Daitokuji in ''[[Project A-Ko]]'' (1986)\n*Kekko Kamen in ''[[Kekko Kamen]]'' (1991)\n*Kyurene (ep. 6), Jumeau (ep. 18), [[Sailor Jupiter|Makoto Kino/Sailor Jupiter]] (eps. 25 - 200), DD Girls V (ep. 45) in ''[[Sailor Moon (TV series)|Pretty Soldier Sailor Moon]]'' (1992)\n*Mirei in ''[[Tokyo Babylon]]'' (1992)\n*Kanako (Kana-chan) in ''[[Miracle Girls]]'' (1993)\n*Isabelle in ''[[Moldiver]]'' (1993)\n*Kagero in ''[[Ninja Scroll]]'' (1993)\n*Makoto Kino/Sailor Jupiter in ''[[Sailor Moon R: The Movie|Pretty Soldier Sailor Moon R The Movie]] (1993)\n*Mokuren in ''[[Please Save My Earth]]'' (1993)\n*Presea and Sierra in ''[[Magic Knight Rayearth]]'' (1994)\n*Makoto Kino/Sailor Jupiter in ''[[Sailor Moon S: The Movie|Pretty Soldier Sailor Moon S The Movie]] (1994)\n*The Mad Hatter in ''[[Miyuki-chan in Wonderland]]'' (1995)\n*Makoto Kino/Sailor Jupiter in ''[[Sailor Moon Supers: The Movie|The 9 Sailor Soldiers Get Together! Miracle in the Black Dream Hole]] (1995)\n*[[April O'Neil]] in ''[[Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles#Anime|Mutant Turtles: Superman Legend]]'' (1996)\n* Ruiko Sakuragi in ''[[Kindaichi Case Files]]'' (1997)\n*Eri Ochiai in ''[[Perfect Blue]]'' (1997)\n*[[Kaho Mizuki]] in ''[[Cardcaptor Sakura]]'' (1998)\n*Yayoi Matsunaga in ''[[Nightwalker: The Midnight Detective|Nightwalker]]'' (1998)\n*Kaho Mizuki in ''[[Cardcaptor Sakura Movie 2: The Sealed Card]]'' (2000)\n*Katsuna Asamiya in ''[[Bleach (anime)|Bleach]]'' (2004)\n*Kushina Uzumaki in ''[[Naruto Shippuuden]]'' (2007)\n*Kaho Mizuki in ''[[Cardcaptor Sakura: Clear Card]]'' (2018)\n\nUnknown date\n*Prince Tapioca in ''[[Princess Quest]]''\n*[[List of Maria-sama ga Miteru characters#Y\u014dko Mizuno|Y\u014dko Mizuno]] in ''[[Maria-sama ga Miteru]]''\n*Xia Yu Fan in ''[[Full Metal Panic! The Second Raid]]''\n*Mitsuko Aida  in ''[[Honey and Clover]]''\n*Karei Hirozaki in ''[[Maburaho]]''\n*Shizuka Namio in ''[[Space Pirate Captain Herlock]] ova''\n*Maria Pia Armonia in ''[[Mobile Suit Victory Gundam]]''\n*[[Tennyo Masaki]] in ''[[Tenchi Muyo!]]'' (OVA 3)\n*Mirage Koas in ''[[Star Ocean: Till the End of Time]]''\n*Namiko Todaka in ''[[Hell Girl]]''\n*Agarte Lindblum in ''[[Tales of Rebirth]]''\n*Ms. Sakagami in ''[[Nana (manga)|Nana]]''\n*[[List of Claymore characters#Ophelia|Ophelia]] in ''[[Claymore (manga)|Claymore]]''\n*V.E in ''[[Summon Night Craft Sword Monogatari: Hajimari no Ishi]]''\n*Tsubura Ise in ''[[Ayakashi Ninden Kunoichiban]]'' (PlayStation