{"title_page": "Naoki Imaya", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2012}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name= Naoki Imaya\n| image =\n| fullname = Naoki Imaya\n| birth_date  = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1980|6|18}}\n| birth_place = Tokyo, Japan\n| height = {{height|m=1.79}}\n| currentclub  = \n| position = [[Striker (football)|Striker]], [[Midfielder (football)|Midfielder]]\n| youthyears1 = \n| youthclubs1 = \n| years1 = 2000 \n| years2 = 2001 \n| years3 = 2002 \n| years4 = 2002 \n| years5 = 2003 \n| years6 = 2003\u20132004 \n| years7 = 2004 \n| years8 = 2005 \n| years9 = 2005\u20132006 \n| years10 = 2006 \n| years11 = 2007\u20132008\n| clubs1 = [[Blacktown City Demons|Blacktown City]] \n| clubs2 = [[Canberra Cosmos]] \n| clubs3 = [[Blacktown City Demons|Blacktown City]] \n| clubs4 = [[Adelaide Galaxy]] \n| clubs5 = [[Blacktown City Demons|Blacktown City]] \n| clubs6 = [[Neuch\u00e2tel Xamax]] \n| clubs7 = [[FC La Chaux-de-Fonds|La Chaux-de-Fonds]] \n| clubs8 = [[Blacktown City Demons|Blacktown City]] \n| clubs9 = [[New Zealand Knights FC|New Zealand Knights]] \n| clubs10 = [[Marconi Stallions]] \n| clubs11 = [[VfB L\u00fcbeck]]\n| caps1 = 25  \n| caps2 = 21  \n| caps3 = 22  \n| caps4 = 10  \n| caps5 = 22  \n| caps6 = 8  \n| caps7 = 12  \n| caps8 = 11  \n| caps9 = 11  \n| caps10 = \n| caps11 = 12  \n| goals1 = 6  \n| goals2 = 3  \n| goals3 = 6  \n| goals4 = 4  \n| goals5 = 1  \n| goals6 = 0  \n| goals7 = 0  \n| goals8 = 4  \n| goals9 = 0  \n| goals10 = \n| goals11 = 0\n}}\n{{Nihongo|'''Naoki Imaya'''|\u4eca\u77e2 \u76f4\u57ce|Imaya Naoki|born 18 June 1980 in Tokyo}} is a former Japanese [[Association football|footballer]] who played as a [[midfielder]] or [[Striker (association football)|forward]].\n\n==Career==\nAs a child he moved to Sydney Australia with his parents at age 10. He played for various Australian clubs before moving to [[Switzerland]]. He played in the first season of the [[A-League]] with the [[New Zealand Knights FC|New Zealand Knights]] before returning to [[NSW]] state league football with [[Marconi Stallions]].<ref>[http://spawningsalmon.blogspot.com/2009/04/naoki-imayas-football-vision.html Naoki Imaya's Football Vision]</ref>\n\nIn July 2007 he signed a contract with [[VfB L\u00fcbeck]], a traditional club from [[L\u00fcbeck]] in the federal state of [[Schleswig-Holstein]] playing in the 3rd German [[Regionalliga Nord]].<ref>[http://www.fussballdaten.de/spieler/imayanaoki/ Naoki Imaya \u2013 Fussballdaten \u2013 Die Fu\u00dfball-Datenbank]</ref> He was released by the club after six months due to financial problems.<ref>[http://www.tribalfootball.com/cultural-divide-changing-between-australia-and-japan-238490 Cultural divide changing between Australia and Japan]</ref>\n\n==Coaching career==\nImaya is now coaching football to young children in Japan and no longer pursuing a professional career.<ref>[http://www.naocastle.com/blog/ Nao Castle]</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://au.fourfourtwo.com/news/100908,naokis-castle.aspx naokis-castle 442]\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Imaya, Naoki}}\n[[Category:1980 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Japanese footballers]]\n[[Category:Japanese expatriate footballers]]\n[[Category:Expatriate association footballers in New Zealand]]\n[[Category:Expatriate soccer players in Australia]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Switzerland]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Germany]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Tokyo]]\n[[Category:A-League players]]\n[[Category:National Soccer League (Australia) players]]\n[[Category:Swiss Super League players]]\n[[Category:Blacktown City FC players]]\n[[Category:Canberra Cosmos players]]\n[[Category:Marconi Stallions FC players]]\n[[Category:Neuch\u00e2tel Xamax FCS players]]\n[[Category:New Zealand Knights FC players]]\n[[Category:VfB L\u00fcbeck players]]\n[[Category:Association football forwards]]\n\n\n{{Japan-footy-forward-1980s-stub}}\n{{Australia-footy-bio-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{